<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>yea good ideas for resist, atk and dam...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tempra[CC]">Tempra[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 3:02 p.m. 9/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> yea good ideas for resist, atk and dam...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=389" TARGET=_self>This is a *HUGE* problem going beyond magic system</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>should be based on the numbers... if i'm lvl 50 and i got 30 resist i should resist the same amount of times as anyone with 30 resist no more or less because of my level. same with attack and defense, if you got the same numbers between the levels you should have the same oppurtunity to hit each other and for you to block. This might be the case... when i was fighting my friend who was a cleric and i being a druid we were pretty equal when he fought me at a lower lvl. Since his attack and defense were both higher then me he was better then me at melee, but in magic it didnt even compare. Melee might be fine the way it is... havent tried if it is level based or number based.

<P>This is the #1 reason why PvP will or won't work in Everquest.
<BR>&gt; I've been beating this drum for months, and if something is not
<BR>&gt; done soon we can essentially write it off as an option.
<P>&gt; The Everquest algorithms for determining ATK, DAM, and spell
<BR>&gt; resistance are based on the PvE design, and incorporate code to
<BR>&gt; prevent rapid levelling and twinking. If you could spell damage
<BR>&gt; MOBs that are 2 or more levels above you just as well as those
<BR>&gt; your own level, then groups of mages could go around at low
<BR>&gt; levels and find ways to exploit and take out powerful creatures
<BR>&gt; for BIG XP gains. I understand what 989 is doing and agree with
<BR>&gt; it for PvE, but is has to GO for PvP!
<P>&gt; Spell resistance, attack, and damage calculations must be
<BR>&gt; modified for PvP specific combat. All three should work much
<BR>&gt; better across a broader range of player levels. If a level 10
<BR>&gt; and a level 20 for some reason both have the same ATK and DAM
<BR>&gt; numbers, and given their AC is the same then they should have
<BR>&gt; the same chances to hit each other and same range of damage
<BR>&gt; available given they are using the same weapon. Resist should be
<BR>&gt; level based but not impossible to effect players 1-2 levels
<BR>&gt; above yourself as is currently.
<P>&gt; Weapons should be largely de-nurfed in PvP as well. For example
<BR>&gt; a weapon with a 13 damage factor is limited to 1-18 until level
<BR>&gt; 10 is reached, at which time it goes to 1-24. At some point I
<BR>&gt; believe it hits 1-32, or at least it did in earlier versions of
<BR>&gt; EQ. The 1-18 weapon probably does even less at low levels but I
<BR>&gt; haven't tried it.
<P>&gt; Once the above issues are addressed there are some improvements
<BR>&gt; that can be made to make PvP better, but I look upon the
<BR>&gt; aforementioned as an absolute necessity to making PvP viable
<BR>&gt; before other measures are taken.
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
